HEADWORD: Consolidant
<hw>Con*sol"i*dant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>consolidans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>consolidare</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>consolidant</ets>.]</ety> <def>Serving to unite or consolidate;
having the quality of consolidating or making firm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

